  <summary date="2021-06-06T02:27:21Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Comprehensive National Mercury Monitoring Act

This bill requires the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) to establish&#160;a national mercury monitoring program. Under the program, the EPA must track and report on long-term changes of mercury concentrations in air, water, soil, and fish and wildlife.&#160;In addition, the EPA must establish an online database for mercury data.</summary>
